            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>udon noodles</strong> to a large bowl, cover them with <strong>boiled water </strong>and set aside to soak for 4-5 min</p><p>Tip: Gently separate the noodles with a fork!</p><p>Drain the <strong>soaked noodles</strong>, reserving 80ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[120ml] </span>of<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>starchy noodle water</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> and <strong>reserved starchy noodle water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> – this is your <strong>soy stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1704803049935-x200.jpg",
