            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once slightly softened, increase the heat to high and add the <strong>soy stock</strong> and cook for 1 min further, then add the<strong> drained</strong> <strong>udon noodles</strong> to the pan with the <strong>pak choi green tops</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the noodles are coated in sauce – these are your <strong>Shanghai-style noodles</strong></p><p>Place the <strong>Chinese-style</strong> <strong>pancakes</strong> (still in their bag) in the <strong>microwave </strong>and heat for 30 secs</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
